{{Infobox person | name = Samuel Fränkel | image = Samuel Fränkel (1801-1881).png | birth_date = 22 November 1801 | birth_place = [[Biała Prudnicka|Zülz]] | death_date = 28 July 1881 (age 79) | death_place = [[Prudnik|Neustadt O.S.]] }} '''Samuel Fränkel''' (22 November 1801 – 28 July 1881<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dobratrasa.eu/pl/misto/dobre-zachovaly-zidovsky-hrbitov-v-prudniku|title=Dobrá trasa - Vydejte se s námi na skok sousedům|website=www.dobratrasa.eu|access-date=2018-11-03}}</ref>) was a German industrialist.
== Life == Samuel Fränkel was born 22 November 1801 in Zülz (currently [[Biała Prudnicka]], [[Poland]]). In 1827 he moved to Neustadt O.S. (currently [[Prudnik]]). He founded a terrycloth factory at the shore of [[Prudnik (river)|Prudnik river]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://prudnik24.pl/index.php/2015/01/13/jak-zmienial-sie-prudnik-z-inicjatywy-rodzin-frankel-pinkus-cz-1/|title=Jak zmieniał się Prudnik z inicjatywy rodzin Fränkel i Pinkus – cz. 1 - Prudnik24|date=2015-01-13|work=Prudnik24|access-date=2018-11-03|language=pl-PL}}</ref>. It quickly became one of the biggest terrycloth factories in [[Europe]]. The company was later known as [[Zakłady Przemysłu Bawełnianego "Frotex"]]. Fränkel opened a few branches in [[Berlin]] and [[Augsburg]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sztetl.org.pl/pl/biogramy/5438-frankel-samuel|title=Fränkel Samuel {{!}} Wirtualny Sztetl|website=sztetl.org.pl|language=pl|access-date=2018-11-03}}</ref>.
Samuel Fränkel died 28 July 1881 in Neustadt O.S. He was a grandfather of [[Max Pinkus]].
